      "writtenOn": "2017-10-03T16:27:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "POSIX doesn’t list EINTR as a possible error code, but it absolutely is with many implementations because of the underlying open(). I think that this should be HANDLE_EINTR(). Except it can’t really be HANDLE_EINTR() because that looks for -1 as the failure value, and here we have (DIR*)nullptr. But I think you get the gist…",
      "revId": "9c11b4ea96413474a9f46dc6ad7aaef89e4b70a1",
