    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "543bdac1_a936aaed",
        "filename": "util/file/directory_reader_posix.cc",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 43,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-03T16:27:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "readdir()/readdir_r() are a little trickier with EINTR, but I think it’d be right to do something like HANDLE_EINTR() for them too to cover EINTR from the underlying getdents() or equivalent. Bionic appears to take care of this on its own already, and an extra layer should be harmless, but you can omit it on OS_ANDROID if you’d like. (https://android.googlesource.com/platform/bionic/+/5edb0f40f654c804d38f1bff43f91719e189c892/libc/bionic/dirent.cpp#96, looks like it’s accounted for EINTR since the very beginning.)\n\nGiven these improvements, you may want to use this DirectoryReader anywhere else that you find an opendir()/readdir()/readdir_r().",
      "revId": "9c11b4ea96413474a9f46dc6ad7aaef89e4b70a1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
