      },
      "lineNbr": 44,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-09T17:53:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done",
      "parentUuid": "fa39247e_0848530e",
      "revId": "9c11b4ea96413474a9f46dc6ad7aaef89e4b70a1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "05015de8_2876c943",
        "filename": "util/file/directory_reader_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 34,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-03T16:27:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Based on some documentation, it sounds like performance will improve if you use FindFirstFileEx() specifying fInfoLevelId \u003d FindExInfoBasic and dwAdditionalFlags \u003d FIND_FIRST_EX_LARGE_FETCH.\n\nScopedTempDir::RecursivelyDeleteTemporaryDirectory() in test/scoped_temp_dir_win.cc could also benefit from that, so you could base it on this new interface too.",
      "revId": "9c11b4ea96413474a9f46dc6ad7aaef89e4b70a1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d658aba1_bdc0e5a6",
        "filename": "util/file/directory_reader_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 34,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-09T17:53:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done",
      "parentUuid": "05015de8_2876c943",
      "revId": "9c11b4ea96413474a9f46dc6ad7aaef89e4b70a1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "590fbfa4_e6f6c41b",
        "filename": "util/file/directory_reader_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 37,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-03T16:27:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If the directory exists but there are no files in it, FindFirstFile() will return ERROR_FILE_NOT_FOUND. In that case, we’d want the Open() to succeed, and for the first NextFile() to return Result::kFileNotFound. (This seems to be what you expect to happen based on the interface you designed and based on how the POSIX implementation works.)\n\nOn the other hand, if the directory doesn’t exist at all, I do think we’d want this to fail. But you might get ERROR_FILE_NOT_FOUND in that case too, so perhaps more work is needed.\n\nYour test should check both of these conditions.",
      "revId": "9c11b4ea96413474a9f46dc6ad7aaef89e4b70a1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "58baa85d_6154067d",
        "filename": "util/file/directory_reader_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 37,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-09T17:53:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My expectation was that FindFirstFile() would always return at least \".\" and \"..\" as long as we use \"*\" to match all files and the directory exists.\n\nThere are tests for empty directories and non-existing directories.",
      "parentUuid": "590fbfa4_e6f6c41b",
      "revId": "9c11b4ea96413474a9f46dc6ad7aaef89e4b70a1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
